Challenge Faced & Solution
Challenge: After setting NTFS permissions, both users initially had the same access level despite correct settings.
Solution: I discovered Share permissions were overriding (Everyone had Full Control). I tightened Share permissions to the specific group and re-tested Effective Access in the folder’s Advanced Security tab. Running gpupdate /force and logging off/on also helped apply changes cleanly. This highlighted the importance of understanding that effective permissions = most restrictive of (Share + NTFS).
